<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca913d22-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2425"><num value="2425">§ 2425.</num><heading> Operations, maintenance, and replacement costs</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d23-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2425/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The non-Federal share of operations, maintenance, and replacement costs for a project receiving Federal assistance under this subchapter shall be 100 percent.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idca913d24-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2425/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Plan</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">On request of the non-Federal borrower, the Secretary may assist in the development of an operation, maintenance, and replacement plan to provide the necessary framework to assist the non-Federal borrower in establishing rates and fees for project beneficiaries.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idca913d25-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/451/tII/s206">Pub. L. 109–451, title II, § 206</ref>, <date date="2006-12-22">Dec. 22, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/3360">120 Stat. 3360</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
